##Diary of an Italian epidemic | a mixture of fear and hope

XISUMJC

MJC Professional Practice Communication Platform for Xi'an International Studies University. A true record of the living conditions of foreigners in Shaanxi and Shaanxi people abroad. With vivid and vivid stories, the cultural separation, collision and communication between self and other under the background of globalization are observed. The state of the other, the state of the visitor.

“Dio ha scelto di stare dalla nostra parte.”

Before February 21, there were only three confirmed cases of new pneumonia in Italy. However, as of March 10, local time, new Italian pneumonia confirmed a cumulative total of 10,149 cases, 631 deaths. Both confirmed cases and deaths have exploded, with Italy becoming the most affected country in Europe and with the highest mortality rate in the world.

A plane from Russia arrives in Milan at 08:28 China Standard Time, through the clouds. In the case of the cancellation of China's direct flight to Milan, Qiu Zhenyu took a high-speed train from Xi'an to Shanghai to take a direct flight to Russia, then transferred to Russia and flew to Milan again. According to the original plan, he returned to the city, continue to start foreign trade work in foreign countries.

"after a long journey, I finally arrived. Good night and best wishes to my motherland. " This was Qiu Zhenyu's first circle of friends after he arrived in Milan. At that time, he did not expect that the Italian epidemic would be so serious a month later.

The outbreak in Italy has already had a serious impact on the northern regions. The two outbreaks of infection are concentrated near the two famous cities of Milan and Venice, the Veneto and Lombardy regions have announced corresponding blockades.

Venice's annual carnival and several Serie A competitions were halted, and schools, museums, opera houses and other public facilities were shut down, in some areas, panic buying of necessities and epidemic prevention supplies has taken place.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Sales of luxury goods in Italy will face a 30 percent drop this year because of the outbreak in China, according to ANSA. The tourist market is also particularly cold, without the Spring Festival holiday passenger flow, the Venice high-end hotel room rate nearly halved.

The streets under the outbreak

Qiu Zhenyu also knows this very well. He is now in a state of suspension because of the epidemic. There are about 300,000 Chinese in Milan, and many local Chinese like him have chosen to stop work and be quarantined at home. Most of the shops run by Chinese have closed, this has a big impact on the Italian economy.

Return to Milan

When Qiu Zhenyu arrived in Milan in early February, it coincided with a domestic outbreak. So when he returned to Milan this time, he was more alert to the outbreak.

"On February 17, my colleagues and I took a train to Milan to deal with work matters. At that time, few people on the train wore masks, " Qiu said of his first trip back to Milan. "But on the train, there were strange eyes looking at us, and even people secretly taking pictures of us. ".

For these, Qiu Zhenyu and his colleagues do not have too much care. So at the end of the day, instead of taking the train, he and his colleagues drove home.

"driving back is our best option, not only to avoid unnecessary misunderstandings and trouble, but also to isolate people and avoid direct contact in public. "

Qiu Zhenyu is also very worried about his and his colleagues'health. Due to medical treatment and policy reasons, once infected with the virus, staying in Italy for treatment afterwards will be a very troublesome thing, this also makes Qiu Zhenyu, who is in a foreign country, attach more importance to the prevention and control of the epidemic.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
At the same time affected by the epidemic, he engaged in foreign trade work has also been a great impact. Usually in Italy he is mainly responsible for logistics and procurement work, need to travel to Milan and other parts of Italy. And with the outbreak in mid-to-late February, Qiu Zhenyu now has to stop work at home epidemic prevention state.

In order to eat and sleep normally during the quarantine, he and his colleagues went to the supermarket to buy some ingredients and necessities such as daily necessities. Qiu Zhenyu said of his psychological state, whether it is on the work, family or their health, are feeling the pressure.

During this period of isolation, he chose to watch movies or read to pass the time, "I recently read a book at Fandeng to calm my mind and use the time to learn English. After all, I can use it to eat and speak English anywhere in the world. ". Through this he made himself stronger and braver in the face of the epidemic, even in isolation, the soul can be free.

The Italian people in Qiu Zhenyu's eyes

"When I came to Milan in early February, it was very different from home, life was as usual, there were no masks on the streets, " Qiu said, adding that many Chinese shops were closing after the confirmed cases on February 21, many of the local shops are still open and the company is still running.

Department Store, Chanel counter

"In late February, there were not many people wearing masks here in Milan, with fewer confirmed cases and low awareness of protection. "They seem to see this epidemic as something more serious than the flu, " said Qiu Zhenyu, whose friend posted a message in an Italian street restaurant on March 7, the restaurant was still full, and no one was wearing a mask.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
A packed Italian restaurant

This was the day before the closure of the city of Milan in Italy, and on March 7, the number of confirmed cases in Italy had reached 5,883. People here are less aware of the epidemic than at home, and the severity of the epidemic is generally underestimated, "because of the different state system, it is very difficult for Italy to keep people at home and not go out, but it is not compulsory to advise people to stay at home and not go out. "

On March 10, Italy announced that "Vassal State" , "the police on the street have been turning around, people are not allowed to run around, and then the La Rinascente building in Milan is closed. " This is a chat between Qiu Zhenyu and his friends, the tense situation in Italy has put everyone in the country on edge.

As the outbreak spread, masks and disinfectant supplies were almost sold out across Italy. The prices of face masks and other products, both online and in brick-and-mortar stores, are also going up like crazy.

"when the domestic epidemic was in an outbreak period, the Chinese found a lot of local pharmacies, sent the masks and other protective products home and donated them back to the country, " Qiu said of the masks, adding that it was difficult to buy them in Italy, these have been sold short, usually 2 euros, 5 euros a pack of face masks now sell in Italy to 50 euros, 100 euros.

Qiu Zhenyu said that his mask is currently brought back from the domestic, but now there is not much left, but also through a friend's channel to buy some masks. "I've been staying at home recently, and I don't think it would be a waste of a mask" . Under such circumstances, Qiu Zhenyu's optimistic attitude towards life can still be seen in his statement.

It is reported that at present, domestic overseas Chinese Federation and other relevant units will support care for overseas Chinese masks, Chinese medicine and rice and other living materials, and provide online medical consultation.

"I will stay here. "

As of 2400 hours on March 9, there were 33 confirmed cases imported from outside Lanzhou, which is related to more than 300 people who have recently returned home from Iran, according to the latest report from China's National Health Commission.

On March 11, there was also an imported case from Italy in Zhengzhou. The situation in the country is gradually improving, medical measures are generally reassuring, and the Italian hospital for new pneumonia patients is serious will be admitted to hospital, the light home self-isolation, medical costs are also personal.

Going home or staying? Qiu Zhenyu said he will continue to stay in Italy, "around the Italian people have many friends to buy air tickets back to the country, but I do not have such plans at present. ".

On the one hand, it is more difficult to return to China. On the other hand, there are many unsafe factors in returning to China at this time. On the way, we do not know what kind of people we will meet, and whether we will be infected or not. Moreover, if we return to China, if we are infected, our families will be affected. It's better to stay at home now, at least away from the dense crowd."after weighing, he chose to stay at home in isolation in Italy.

In Qiu Zhenyu's view, although going home is everyone's most instinctive choice when faced with danger and disaster, he still chose to stay in Italy, "If you look at the situation now, many people back to the diagnosis, there are also people who lied about their travel, which is also an irresponsible performance for the safety of others. ".

I hope it's GonNa be okay

In the face of the virus, there are no borders, which is a common human challenge. Qiu Zhenyu has been working in Italy for more than a year, from the domestic outbreak to the Italian epidemic, these are unexpected.

"every life is precious under the epidemic. Foreign Trade is also vulnerable, and many things can not go on. I hope the epidemic in Italy will get better soon. " In a foreign country, he faced a severe epidemic in Italy, qiu Zhenyu's heart is afraid but still full of hope, hope for work, hope for life, hope for life.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
En route to Shanghai airport

Finally, Qiu Zhenyu lamented that in this special place and period, more comes from the pride and pride of the motherland, "In the face of the epidemic, our government acted promptly, the control effect was very good, the people were very cooperative and felt the great cohesion of the nation. "

The day after Qiu Zhenyu was interviewed, Italy sent out a notice to close the city, and now Italy has closed the country, and urgent help to China. I hope that at this time in Italy, whether it is work, school or other people have to raise awareness of protection, to protect themselves.

Italy under the "State Blockade"
